Ruby people really don&rsquo;t like CSS do they? But Less is actually pretty cool. It&rsquo;s basically an attempt to bootstrap features, specifically Variables, Mixins, Operations and Nested Rules, into CSS. The best part about this is it uses CSS syntax and a simple one step compiler. I&rsquo;d be interested to know what the folks at the W3C think about this.
So for instance you can do:
pre. /* LESS */ brand_color: #4D926F; #header { color:brand_color; } h2 { color: @brand_color; }

